"slide-imageSource"><span class="credit manualSource">©Ignacy Matusewski</span></div></div></li><li class="carousel-item"><noscript data-src="http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/ebf8425c-8d30-47ef-ae3a-05d34d55846e.img" data-alt="" data-width="600" data-height="338"><img src="http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/ebf8425c-8d30-47ef-ae3a-05d34d55846e.img" alt="" width="600" height="338" /></noscript><div class="slide-overlay">A view of the estate from the doorway of a prewar building<div class="slide-imageSource"><span class="credit manualSource">©Grazyna Rutowska National Digital Archive Pol</span></div></div></li><li class="carousel-item"><noscript data-src="http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/255e48ba-72a6-4e84-aba0-c8d6a5d83b2a.img" data-alt="" data-width="600" data-height="338"><img src="http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/255e48ba-72a6-4e84-aba0-c8d6a5d83b2a.img" alt="" width="600" height="338" /></noscript><div class="slide-overlay">Palace of Culture and Science, built in 1952-1955, next to the Złote Tarasy (Golden Terraces) shopping centre, built in 2007<div class="slide-imageSource"><span class="credit manualSource">©4Corners</span></div></div></li><li class="carousel-item"><noscript data-src="http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/e7311a6f-9c3f-425a-9bd1-d2342ae9e366.img" data-alt="" data-width="600" data-height="338"><img src="http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/e7311a6f-9c3f-425a-9bd1-d2342ae9e366.img" alt="" width="600" height="338" /></noscript><div class="slide-overlay">A painted apartment block on Grojecka street in the city’s Ochata district, 2014<div class="slide-imageSource"><span class="credit manualSource">©Marcin Kadzialko</span></div></div></li><li class="carousel-item"><noscript data-src="http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/5a9c104d-2766-49a9-bcbc-284ae00e6401.img" data-alt="" data-width="600" data-height="338"><img src="http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/5a9c104d-2766-49a9-bcbc-284ae00e6401.img" alt="" width="600" height="